ce:section.ce:para:
The developed smartphone-assisted N-CQDs/Eu3+-based ratiometric FL sensor was applied to detect OTC in pork samples. As presented in Table 1
                        , the smartphone-based N-CQDs/Eu3+-based ratiometric FL sensor achieved good OTC detection results (96.89–103.20%) and reasonable relative standard deviation (RSD) (0.20–1.68%). The intraday and interday repeatability of the testing system was evaluated according to the guidelines established by the FDA [67]. The stability data indicate that the method remains relatively stable for a short duration at both −20 °C and 23 °C (Table 2
                        ). Consequently, the method can be effectively applied to samples stored at room temperature or kept frozen for short periods.
